WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:17.540 --> 00:00:21.830
I've cried my heart out.
And I've whined more than enough.

3
00:00:23.960 --> 00:00:25.460
My mind is made up!

4
00:00:27.380 --> 00:00:30.970
I have to go. Everyone's fighting!

5
00:00:32.350 --> 00:00:35.350
Come on! Live, dammit!

6
00:00:39.560 --> 00:00:42.940
Hurry and wake up
before it's too late!

7
00:00:42.940 --> 00:00:46.650
Your friends... Your friends are...!

8
00:00:51.410 --> 00:00:57.830
I thought for sure they had a chance
against him... How could this happen?

9
00:00:58.710 --> 00:01:01.000
What did that damn shark just do?

10
00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:02.290
I don't know.

11
00:01:02.710 --> 00:01:07.090
I thought he just sprayed them with water,
but now they're coughing up blood!

12
00:01:08.670 --> 00:01:11.340
All I need is a few drops of water,

13
00:01:11.340 --> 00:01:16.930
and I can kill you lowly humans
without even touching you.

14
00:01:16.930 --> 00:01:19.020
That's what separates our races.

15
00:01:19.020 --> 00:01:20.180
Give me a break!

16
00:01:26.980 --> 00:01:29.240
This is no joke...

17
00:01:29.240 --> 00:01:35.070
A splash of water from him
feels like getting hit with a shotgun!

18
00:01:35.070 --> 00:01:37.200
I can't believe a shark
has this much power...

19
00:01:37.200 --> 00:01:40.290
Even among fishmen,
he's in a league of his own...

20
00:01:43.710 --> 00:01:45.590
He's on another level...

21
00:01:45.590 --> 00:01:47.550
Just die already.

22
00:01:47.920 --> 00:01:52.510
Nothing of value was lost.
After all, your lives are meaningless.

23
00:01:52.510 --> 00:01:53.470
Arlong!

24
00:01:54.300 --> 00:01:56.100
– Big Sis Nami!
– Big Sis Nami!

25
00:01:56.100 --> 00:01:57.100
Nami!

26
00:01:57.100 --> 00:01:59.060
– Nami...
– It's Nami...

27
00:01:59.060 --> 00:02:04.980
Yo, Nami! I was just about
to crush these two-bit pirates.

28
00:02:04.980 --> 00:02:07.320
Why'd you come here?

29
00:02:12.570 --> 00:02:14.410
To kill you.

30
00:02:16.570 --> 00:02:18.700
Wealth, fame, power...

31
00:02:18.700 --> 00:02:22.870
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates,
obtained everything the world has to offer.

32
00:02:22.870 --> 00:02:26.710
What he said in his final moments
drove countless souls to the seas.

33
00:02:26.710 --> 00:02:28.710
You want my treasure?

34
00:02:28.710 --> 00:02:30.500
Go ahead.

35
00:02:30.500 --> 00:02:31.710
Find it!

36
00:02:31.710 --> 00:02:34.300
Everything is right where I left it!

37
00:02:36.720 --> 00:02:41.430
People set their sights on the Grand Line
in pursuit of their dreams.

38
00:02:41.430 --> 00:02:44.680
The world has truly entered
the Great Pirate Era!

39
00:02:45.440 --> 00:02:50.690
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

40
00:02:50.900 --> 00:02:56.490
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for

41
00:02:56.820 --> 00:02:57.740
One Piece!

42
00:03:02.950 --> 00:03:07.750
Compasses? Not for me. Left them all behind

43
00:03:08.630 --> 00:03:13.550
I'm headed out to sea, with my heart serving as guide

44
00:03:14.380 --> 00:03:19.590
Following the ancient map to the spot marked "X" reveals

45
00:03:19.590 --> 00:03:24.810
Yeah, it's only legendary till someone proves it's real

46
00:03:26.430 --> 00:03:28.760
When the world's got you down,

47
00:03:28.760 --> 00:03:31.900
lean on your crew, they'll turn it around

48
00:03:32.230 --> 00:03:37.240
Their biorhythm will carry you through

49
00:03:37.450 --> 00:03:39.280
We're gonna make the most of it

50
00:03:41.160 --> 00:03:46.450
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

51
00:03:46.660 --> 00:03:52.040
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for

52
00:03:52.380 --> 00:03:55.090
Got some change to my name,

53
00:03:55.090 --> 00:03:58.300
and maybe you wanna be my friend?

54
00:03:58.590 --> 00:04:03.180
We are, we are on the cruise!

55
00:04:03.970 --> 00:04:04.810
WE ARE!

56
00:04:05.100 --> 00:04:09.020
<b>My Turn</b>

57
00:04:07.560 --> 00:04:09.020
To kill...

58
00:04:09.650 --> 00:04:11.270
me?

59
00:04:15.610 --> 00:04:17.990
You never learn, do you?

60
00:04:18.360 --> 00:04:22.740
How many times did you try to kill me
during the eight years you were with us?

61
00:04:23.950 --> 00:04:27.710
You tried assassination,
poison, even ambushes...

62
00:04:27.710 --> 00:04:29.670
but I'm still here.

63
00:04:30.920 --> 00:04:36.090
You should know by now that mere
humans like you can never kill me.

64
00:04:37.170 --> 00:04:40.090
Now, listen. I won't kill you...

65
00:04:41.180 --> 00:04:44.850
but you'll never escape me, either.

66
00:04:45.520 --> 00:04:46.600
Nami...

67
00:04:47.430 --> 00:04:51.150
You'll be our cartographer forever.

68
00:04:52.730 --> 00:04:56.440
But, as you know,
I'm a reasonable man.

69
00:04:56.440 --> 00:05:01.110
If possible, I want you to be our
cartographer of your own free will.

70
00:05:05.370 --> 00:05:08.290
So, how about this?

71
00:05:08.750 --> 00:05:15.290
I intend to kill everyone
here except for you.

72
00:05:17.000 --> 00:05:21.630
However, if you willingly come
back to the Arlong Pirates

73
00:05:21.630 --> 00:05:24.470
and draw sea charts
as one of our officers,

74
00:05:25.350 --> 00:05:30.430
I could be convinced to spare
the people of Cocoyashi Village.

75
00:05:31.940 --> 00:05:35.860
Not these two, though.

76
00:05:36.610 --> 00:05:38.440
They went too far.

77
00:05:38.440 --> 00:05:40.610
The question is,
who will you side with?

78
00:05:41.570 --> 00:05:45.580
Will you join me while you still can
and be spared along with the villagers?

79
00:05:46.240 --> 00:05:50.790
Or will you join these weaklings
and try fighting me together?

80
00:05:50.790 --> 00:05:55.670
Though... with the people
you're betting on in this kind of shape,

81
00:05:55.670 --> 00:05:58.920
there's no way this story
of yours has a happy ending.

82
00:06:01.670 --> 00:06:02.970
Nami...

83
00:06:03.550 --> 00:06:06.300
Are you with me?

84
00:06:06.300 --> 00:06:07.390
Or...

85
00:06:07.930 --> 00:06:09.890
are you with them?

86
00:06:12.770 --> 00:06:14.560
This isn't fair...

87
00:06:14.940 --> 00:06:17.270
If I say I'm on Luffy's side...

88
00:06:17.270 --> 00:06:18.770
he'll kill everyone.

89
00:06:19.320 --> 00:06:21.280
But if I say I'm on Arlong's side...

90
00:06:21.280 --> 00:06:23.450
everyone from the
village will be saved.

91
00:06:23.910 --> 00:06:26.450
Everything hinges on what I say next!

92
00:06:29.290 --> 00:06:30.410
How despicable!

93
00:06:30.410 --> 00:06:33.250
Either choice keeps Nami in chains!

94
00:06:35.210 --> 00:06:36.670
Still!

95
00:06:41.380 --> 00:06:42.340
Luffy...

96
00:06:43.670 --> 00:06:45.050
Help me...

97
00:06:45.640 --> 00:06:48.100
Of course I will!

98
00:06:51.560 --> 00:06:55.060
I have to believe in him!

99
00:06:59.070 --> 00:07:00.150
Guys, I'm sorry!

100
00:07:00.520 --> 00:07:03.360
Please die with me!

101
00:07:05.400 --> 00:07:07.620
– All right!
– All right!

102
00:07:07.620 --> 00:07:09.160
Let's do this!

103
00:07:10.410 --> 00:07:12.790
Let's give 'em what for!

104
00:07:13.830 --> 00:07:15.460
So that's how it is...

105
00:07:15.460 --> 00:07:18.790
I guess you all want to die.

106
00:07:25.970 --> 00:07:27.840
P-Please! Please!

107
00:07:28.720 --> 00:07:32.310
Live! Live! Live! Live! Live!

108
00:07:41.150 --> 00:07:42.150
Hm?

109
00:07:42.480 --> 00:07:43.570
What the...?

110
00:07:46.740 --> 00:07:47.450
Finally...!

111
00:07:48.030 --> 00:07:50.700
All that's left is to free his legs...

112
00:07:50.700 --> 00:07:51.700
Oh...?

113
00:07:53.830 --> 00:07:55.330
So that's what you meant...

114
00:07:55.960 --> 00:07:57.080
Could it be?!

115
00:07:57.080 --> 00:07:58.710
Big Bro Luffy!

116
00:07:58.710 --> 00:07:59.710
What?!

117
00:08:00.080 --> 00:08:01.840
Hey, hang in there!

118
00:08:01.840 --> 00:08:03.670
Come back to us!

119
00:08:15.600 --> 00:08:16.980
Thirty seconds!

120
00:08:16.980 --> 00:08:18.560
I won't last longer than that.

121
00:08:21.440 --> 00:08:22.400
Zoro!

122
00:08:23.020 --> 00:08:24.230
That'll be plenty!

123
00:08:26.570 --> 00:08:29.530
There shouldn't be
a fountain over there...

124
00:08:29.530 --> 00:08:31.530
Is it that rubber pest?

125
00:08:36.950 --> 00:08:38.370
Don't worry about that.

126
00:08:38.370 --> 00:08:40.670
It's nothing, you damn half-fish!

127
00:08:41.710 --> 00:08:46.340
I warned you not to
say those words ever again...

128
00:08:46.340 --> 00:08:48.630
You're a dead man walking, Zoro!

129
00:08:53.970 --> 00:08:58.060
If I can smash that block
with a kick, he can go crazy.

130
00:08:58.060 --> 00:09:01.900
Luffy, you're the only one
who can settle this now!

131
00:09:04.980 --> 00:09:09.860
Those with devil fruit powers are
unable to use them in the sea,

132
00:09:09.860 --> 00:09:13.280
and without even the energy
to struggle, they die.

133
00:09:14.030 --> 00:09:16.870
If he's still alive...

134
00:09:16.870 --> 00:09:21.040
that means someone is
raining on our little parade.

135
00:09:21.370 --> 00:09:22.540
Are you all right?!

136
00:09:22.540 --> 00:09:23.960
I thought we lost you!

137
00:09:24.290 --> 00:09:25.880
Yeah! Huh?

138
00:09:25.880 --> 00:09:27.050
What?! What's the matter?!

139
00:09:28.340 --> 00:09:30.090
Where did your pinwheel go?

140
00:09:30.090 --> 00:09:31.090
It was so cool.

141
00:09:31.090 --> 00:09:33.470
Who cares about that right now?!

142
00:09:34.760 --> 00:09:36.850
Raining on our parade?

143
00:09:36.850 --> 00:09:39.930
This game of yours was
rigged from the start.

144
00:09:40.350 --> 00:09:44.480
At any rate, if something's getting
in the way, I need to check it out.

145
00:09:45.730 --> 00:09:46.730
Move.

146
00:09:48.360 --> 00:09:49.400
Egg Star!

147
00:09:52.570 --> 00:09:54.530
I've got your back, Zoro!

148
00:09:55.030 --> 00:09:56.410
Big Bro Usopp!

149
00:09:56.410 --> 00:09:57.540
Is he all right?!

150
00:09:57.540 --> 00:10:00.870
How brave! What a grand entrance!

151
00:10:01.250 --> 00:10:03.250
Don't hold back!

152
00:10:03.250 --> 00:10:05.330
– That's where you are?!
– That's where you are?!

153
00:10:06.090 --> 00:10:07.290
Usopp!

154
00:10:07.800 --> 00:10:09.050
Guess what, Nami!

155
00:10:09.050 --> 00:10:10.630
I beat one of their officers!

156
00:10:10.630 --> 00:10:13.760
One of their officers! Me! I beat him!

157
00:10:14.140 --> 00:10:17.220
Hey, can't you get out
of this on your own?

158
00:10:17.220 --> 00:10:18.640
Oh, no can do.

159
00:10:18.640 --> 00:10:20.470
I'm totally pooped.

160
00:10:20.980 --> 00:10:24.310
Come on! Come on! Come on!

161
00:10:27.480 --> 00:10:29.190
Big Bro Cook!

162
00:10:29.690 --> 00:10:32.490
I don't know what's
going on in the water,

163
00:10:32.490 --> 00:10:35.320
but whatever he's doing
must be the key!

164
00:10:35.320 --> 00:10:36.620
Big Bro Zoro!

165
00:10:37.120 --> 00:10:39.450
Stand firm and stop Arlong!

166
00:10:41.620 --> 00:10:42.960
Okay!

167
00:10:42.960 --> 00:10:47.080
We just have to stop Arlong from
going into the water somehow, huh?

168
00:10:47.080 --> 00:10:49.040
I'll stop him from moving.

169
00:10:53.050 --> 00:10:56.680
I won't let you have your way...!

170
00:10:57.090 --> 00:10:59.640
Hey, Arlong! Over here!

171
00:11:02.100 --> 00:11:04.350
Wha...?! Big Bro Usopp!

172
00:11:04.350 --> 00:11:05.690
How brave!

173
00:11:07.770 --> 00:11:09.610
Usopp...

174
00:11:09.980 --> 00:11:11.570
Rubber Band of Doom!

175
00:11:10.110 --> 00:11:12.480
If you're standing in my way,

176
00:11:12.480 --> 00:11:16.320
that must mean you want
to die first, Roronoa Zoro.

177
00:11:16.700 --> 00:11:18.700
Now! Go, Zoro!

178
00:11:18.700 --> 00:11:20.780
What are you trying to do?!

179
00:11:23.410 --> 00:11:28.130
I'll break that nose you're so proud of!

180
00:11:32.250 --> 00:11:33.630
You fool.

181
00:11:33.630 --> 00:11:36.970
I'm proud of it because
it's unbreakable.

182
00:11:38.220 --> 00:11:41.180
If you were at your full strength,

183
00:11:41.560 --> 00:11:44.890
you might've been able to scratch it.

184
00:12:00.030 --> 00:12:01.450
Big Bro!

185
00:12:01.450 --> 00:12:02.990
Look over there!

186
00:12:02.990 --> 00:12:04.040
Hm?

187
00:12:04.660 --> 00:12:07.000
Oh, crap! That eight-legged
freak is up!

188
00:12:09.210 --> 00:12:11.540
And... what's he doing?

189
00:12:14.420 --> 00:12:17.590
Dammit! I thought the rubber
band was going to hit me!

190
00:12:17.590 --> 00:12:18.970
– What?!
– What?!

191
00:12:18.970 --> 00:12:21.550
What?!

192
00:12:23.060 --> 00:12:26.270
See?! He was my target all along!

193
00:12:26.270 --> 00:12:28.520
You yelled, "Arlong," didn't you?

194
00:12:29.900 --> 00:12:30.980
The octopus...

195
00:12:31.690 --> 00:12:32.940
Roronoa Zoro!

196
00:12:33.320 --> 00:12:36.320
I won't let you have your way!

197
00:12:36.320 --> 00:12:39.990
I'll crush your buddy in the water!

198
00:12:47.080 --> 00:12:51.880
No need to worry. You'll all
be dead soon, after all.

199
00:12:58.970 --> 00:13:01.550
– Big Bro!
– Big Bro!

200
00:13:10.100 --> 00:13:11.850
It's Nami's sister!

201
00:13:11.850 --> 00:13:13.440
Leave the rest to me!

202
00:13:17.740 --> 00:13:18.740
A fishman!

203
00:13:21.030 --> 00:13:22.410
Get back, Nojiko!

204
00:13:22.410 --> 00:13:24.120
I'll break that rock with one kick!

205
00:13:30.410 --> 00:13:31.040
The octopus!

206
00:13:31.370 --> 00:13:34.840
Takoyaki Punch!

207
00:13:35.170 --> 00:13:36.380
Nojiko!

208
00:13:41.630 --> 00:13:43.470
Zoro!

209
00:13:47.430 --> 00:13:49.560
Already out of steam?

210
00:13:49.560 --> 00:13:51.390
What a disappointment.

211
00:13:52.350 --> 00:13:54.860
What's under all these bandages?

212
00:13:57.320 --> 00:13:59.650
Did you have a bad fall or something?

213
00:14:03.950 --> 00:14:06.450
What's with this wound?

214
00:14:20.340 --> 00:14:23.340
How can he still be alive
in this condition?

215
00:14:24.050 --> 00:14:26.930
How can he still be standing?!

216
00:14:38.360 --> 00:14:40.320
What is that look in his eyes?

217
00:14:41.150 --> 00:14:43.570
Are these the eyes of a dying man?

218
00:14:45.700 --> 00:14:47.830
I definitely need
to take this man out...

219
00:14:48.330 --> 00:14:53.290
right here, right now!

220
00:15:00.170 --> 00:15:02.460
Staying still...

221
00:15:02.460 --> 00:15:05.300
would have kept some of
the wounds from opening.

222
00:15:05.300 --> 00:15:08.050
That goes without saying.

223
00:15:08.050 --> 00:15:10.220
You find your situation amusing?

224
00:15:13.810 --> 00:15:16.230
I'm not talking about me...

225
00:15:16.850 --> 00:15:18.520
I'm talking about the octofreak.

226
00:15:19.770 --> 00:15:20.900
What?!

227
00:15:20.900 --> 00:15:22.110
Like we told you...

228
00:15:22.650 --> 00:15:25.320
we win your little game!

229
00:15:35.120 --> 00:15:37.830
Dammit!

230
00:15:37.830 --> 00:15:40.540
That scared the crap outta me!

231
00:15:44.260 --> 00:15:47.760
You're the one who complicated
everything in the first place!

232
00:15:50.550 --> 00:15:51.680
He did it!

233
00:15:52.010 --> 00:15:54.180
Get outta here, you blockhead!

234
00:15:54.600 --> 00:15:57.140
Go kick that stupid shark's ass!

235
00:15:59.100 --> 00:16:00.730
Are you free, kid?!

236
00:16:00.730 --> 00:16:02.730
I sure am!

237
00:16:12.660 --> 00:16:15.370
I'm back!

238
00:16:17.830 --> 00:16:19.290
Rubber boy!

239
00:16:19.670 --> 00:16:22.250
Big Bro Luffy!

240
00:16:29.090 --> 00:16:29.930
Luffy!

241
00:16:33.560 --> 00:16:35.600
That rubber piece of trash...!

242
00:16:36.890 --> 00:16:38.600
You're late, idiot!

243
00:16:40.900 --> 00:16:41.440
Zoro!

244
00:16:42.310 --> 00:16:42.810
Huh?

245
00:16:43.570 --> 00:16:45.320
Hey! Stop it!

246
00:16:45.320 --> 00:16:46.280
You wouldn't...!

247
00:16:50.910 --> 00:16:52.530
My turn now!

248
00:16:54.740 --> 00:16:56.660
– You idiot!
– You idiot!

249
00:16:57.160 --> 00:16:59.120
Gum-Gum...

250
00:16:59.710 --> 00:17:01.830
Bell!

251
00:17:02.540 --> 00:17:03.290
And...

252
00:17:03.290 --> 00:17:05.460
Whip!

253
00:17:12.090 --> 00:17:14.050
Gum-Gum...

254
00:17:14.050 --> 00:17:16.010
Pistol!

255
00:17:20.310 --> 00:17:21.850
Gatling!

256
00:17:31.740 --> 00:17:32.740
Alright!

257
00:17:49.720 --> 00:17:52.010
Did you do something?

258
00:17:52.380 --> 00:17:54.600
– It's not working!
– It's not working!

259
00:17:55.390 --> 00:17:57.760
Yep. That was my warm-up.

260
00:17:59.810 --> 00:18:01.730
That idiot...!

261
00:18:01.730 --> 00:18:03.020
I'll kill him...!

262
00:18:06.940 --> 00:18:11.110
It's admirable how you lowlifes have
held on by the skin of your teeth.

263
00:18:11.740 --> 00:18:16.330
Though, you'd have been happier
dying at the bottom of the sea.

264
00:18:16.330 --> 00:18:17.780
Huh? Nah.

265
00:18:17.780 --> 00:18:20.500
I'm glad they saved me.

266
00:18:23.790 --> 00:18:26.500
Can you understand my fury?

267
00:18:26.880 --> 00:18:31.130
It's the fury of a man who has seen
his dear brothers crushed by worms.

268
00:18:31.130 --> 00:18:36.760
You'll soon wish that you had
quietly submitted to your deaths.

269
00:18:37.260 --> 00:18:40.020
Is Big Bro Luffy gonna be okay?

270
00:18:40.020 --> 00:18:43.390
That crazy barrage
didn't faze him at all.

271
00:18:43.390 --> 00:18:47.230
More importantly, how far
did Big Bro Zoro fly?!

272
00:18:47.610 --> 00:18:50.860
Get him, Luffy! I've got your back!

273
00:18:50.860 --> 00:18:52.440
You're not helping.

274
00:18:59.700 --> 00:19:03.660
If he loses, you're all gonna die, too.

275
00:19:04.160 --> 00:19:05.870
Yeah, we will...

276
00:19:05.870 --> 00:19:08.460
It'll be the end of the East Blue, too.

277
00:19:15.470 --> 00:19:18.930
What's the stark difference
between you and me?

278
00:19:20.310 --> 00:19:21.180
Our noses.

279
00:19:24.390 --> 00:19:25.350
Our jaws?

280
00:19:27.730 --> 00:19:30.190
I wonder if Big Bro's joking...

281
00:19:30.190 --> 00:19:33.150
No... He's definitely serious.

282
00:19:33.530 --> 00:19:34.610
The webs!

283
00:19:35.950 --> 00:19:37.990
It's our race!

284
00:19:50.960 --> 00:19:53.420
That moron hurt himself
when he bit that rock!

285
00:19:53.420 --> 00:19:55.670
Now his teeth are crack–

286
00:19:59.180 --> 00:20:02.890
He crushed the pillar with his teeth!

287
00:20:02.890 --> 00:20:05.230
Ahh! That's scary!

288
00:20:18.820 --> 00:20:19.910
Do you see...

289
00:20:21.280 --> 00:20:23.910
the inherent power of a fishman?

290
00:20:23.910 --> 00:20:28.620
Heaven created you humans
to prostrate yourselves before fishmen.

291
00:20:30.130 --> 00:20:32.750
You're inferior creatures.

292
00:20:32.750 --> 00:20:36.590
We're on a different level
from the moment we're born.

293
00:20:46.640 --> 00:20:52.020
It's true that humans can't crush
a thick pillar like that with their teeth.

294
00:20:52.020 --> 00:20:55.860
If that jaw gets you, it won't
just leave bite marks...

295
00:21:00.820 --> 00:21:03.580
it'll tear clear through your bones!

296
00:21:07.750 --> 00:21:09.750
So what?!

297
00:21:10.170 --> 00:21:11.420
Stop...

298
00:21:13.290 --> 00:21:15.550
bragging about stuff like that!

299
00:21:18.420 --> 00:21:21.590
It's not like biting is the only
way to break stone.

300
00:21:26.260 --> 00:21:28.480
Nice! Score one for Big Bro Luffy!

301
00:21:28.480 --> 00:21:31.100
That's right! The result is the same!

302
00:21:32.350 --> 00:21:35.270
Th-That's beside the point!

303
00:21:35.900 --> 00:21:38.900
Humans are just a stupid,
illogical, and foolish race!

304
00:21:38.900 --> 00:21:42.160
If you fell in the water,
you couldn't even pull yourself out!

305
00:21:42.160 --> 00:21:43.410
What can you do?!

306
00:21:46.950 --> 00:21:51.620
Nothing! That's why I have
help from my friends!

307
00:21:56.380 --> 00:21:58.840
Hm? He can use swords too?

308
00:22:02.550 --> 00:22:03.680
Take that... and that!

309
00:22:03.680 --> 00:22:05.800
What're you doing?

310
00:22:05.800 --> 00:22:10.430
It looks like you're just randomly
swinging those blades around.

311
00:22:18.360 --> 00:22:20.860
I'm not looking
to play your little game.

312
00:22:30.410 --> 00:22:32.120
I've had enough of this nonsense...

313
00:22:32.120 --> 00:22:34.830
Clench your teeth!

314
00:22:56.020 --> 00:22:59.400
– Wha...?! He shattered Arlong's teeth!
– Wha...?! He shattered Arlong's teeth!

315
00:23:02.860 --> 00:23:06.990
I don't know how to use
swords, you bastard!

316
00:23:06.990 --> 00:23:10.200
Huh? What the hell
is he talking about?

317
00:23:13.870 --> 00:23:16.080
I don't know how to navigate.

318
00:23:17.380 --> 00:23:19.130
I can't cook...

319
00:23:20.380 --> 00:23:22.130
I can't lie, either...

320
00:23:22.130 --> 00:23:23.010
Hey.

321
00:23:23.380 --> 00:23:27.090
There's no way I can
make it without help!

322
00:23:31.510 --> 00:23:34.980
Fully admitting just how
pathetic you are...

323
00:23:34.980 --> 00:23:37.150
I guess you never lie
through your teeth.

324
00:23:37.810 --> 00:23:42.480
I pity your crew. Having an
incompetent captain like you...

325
00:23:42.480 --> 00:23:45.070
must be a real pain in the ass.

326
00:23:45.860 --> 00:23:51.580
I can't imagine why they'd
try so desperately to save you...

327
00:23:52.040 --> 00:23:57.710
How can someone like you, without
an ounce of pride, be a pirate captain?

328
00:23:57.710 --> 00:24:00.790
What in the world can you even do?

329
00:24:01.290 --> 00:24:02.920
I can beat you!

330
00:24:06.130 --> 00:24:08.130
That's right, you idiot!

331
00:24:08.470 --> 00:24:11.100
If he dies, I'm gonna kill him!

332
00:24:11.930 --> 00:24:14.060
I've got your back!

333
00:24:14.060 --> 00:24:16.690
That's it, Gum-Gum!

334
00:24:16.690 --> 00:24:18.810
Get him, Big Bro Luffy!

335
00:24:18.810 --> 00:24:21.310
You've got this! You're on
the same level by a hair!

336
00:24:21.310 --> 00:24:24.570
Go to hell, worm!

337
00:24:25.900 --> 00:24:28.490
Ack! He grew new teeth!

338
00:24:28.490 --> 00:24:32.490
I'm a shark. New teeth
grow in one after another.

339
00:24:32.490 --> 00:24:36.450
And they're sturdier
than the previous set.

340
00:24:38.790 --> 00:24:40.420
Each and every time!

341
00:24:44.800 --> 00:24:46.380
Whoa!

342
00:24:46.380 --> 00:24:48.050
As many times as I want!

343
00:24:55.470 --> 00:24:59.440
The heavens have
bestowed this trait upon us.

344
00:25:01.060 --> 00:25:02.440
That's amazing!

345
00:25:03.310 --> 00:25:08.400
Are you starting to realize just how
superior a race the fishmen are?

346
00:25:12.700 --> 00:25:15.330
Tooth and Gum!

347
00:25:15.330 --> 00:25:16.750
Huh?

348
00:25:21.460 --> 00:25:22.080
Stop!

349
00:25:31.050 --> 00:25:33.090
– Big Bro Luffy!
– Big Bro Luffy!

350
00:25:42.480 --> 00:25:44.400
A-Arlong...

351
00:25:45.400 --> 00:25:46.610
That hurt...

352
00:25:46.610 --> 00:25:48.860
Wh-Wha...?! B-Brother!

353
00:25:50.490 --> 00:25:51.490
Phew...

354
00:25:52.240 --> 00:25:54.950
You damn rubber punk!

355
00:25:56.160 --> 00:25:59.950
How dare you use my
brother as a shield?!

356
00:26:00.330 --> 00:26:01.960
What're you talking about?

357
00:26:01.960 --> 00:26:03.920
You're the one who attacked.

358
00:26:03.920 --> 00:26:06.880
Phew... That sure was scary.

359
00:26:11.170 --> 00:26:13.430
Don't move...

360
00:26:13.430 --> 00:26:15.100
you rubber bastard!

361
00:26:17.010 --> 00:26:17.640
Oh, yeah!

362
00:26:17.640 --> 00:26:19.270
I've got a fun idea.

363
00:26:19.270 --> 00:26:20.980
A fun idea?

364
00:26:21.560 --> 00:26:23.270
What in the world is he gonna do?

365
00:26:23.770 --> 00:26:25.940
Does he have some
trick up his sleeve?

366
00:26:27.230 --> 00:26:29.280
Tooth and Gum!

367
00:26:53.220 --> 00:26:54.380
There we go!

368
00:26:56.800 --> 00:26:57.970
Fool...

369
00:26:59.260 --> 00:27:02.230
Crush my teeth all you want...

370
00:27:03.640 --> 00:27:05.770
It won't make any difference!

371
00:27:07.020 --> 00:27:08.770
B-Big Bro Luffy,

372
00:27:08.770 --> 00:27:11.230
surely you didn't mean
that this is your fun idea...

373
00:27:11.230 --> 00:27:14.490
Look! I've got fangs, too!

374
00:27:19.200 --> 00:27:22.750
– S-So he didn't have a trick up his sleeve?
– S-So he didn't have a trick up his sleeve?

375
00:27:26.620 --> 00:27:28.670
How long are you going to keep...

376
00:27:29.040 --> 00:27:31.210
fooling around?!

377
00:27:33.840 --> 00:27:36.550
Shark attack! I've been bit!

378
00:27:37.390 --> 00:27:39.640
– That's because you're playing around!
– That's because you're playing around!

379
00:27:40.350 --> 00:27:42.810
I'm not trying to mess around.

380
00:27:42.810 --> 00:27:44.980
Tooth and Gum!

381
00:28:08.500 --> 00:28:09.880
– Arlong bit him!
– Arlong bit him!

382
00:28:17.720 --> 00:28:20.470
How do you like that?
A tooth for a tooth!

383
00:28:22.180 --> 00:28:24.680
You can use my teeth all you want.

384
00:28:25.930 --> 00:28:28.390
You're still stuck with that weak jaw.

385
00:28:29.150 --> 00:28:29.900
Listen up.

386
00:28:30.650 --> 00:28:35.780
A shark's bite can only rip through
flesh thanks to its powerful jaw!

387
00:28:35.780 --> 00:28:37.950
Teeth alone won't cut it!

388
00:28:39.910 --> 00:28:42.620
Ahh! Big Bro's gonna lose his arm!

389
00:28:43.080 --> 00:28:44.490
Luffy!

390
00:28:51.980 --> 00:28:56.970
More feelings than I can hold but I can’t make you understand

391
00:28:56.990 --> 00:29:01.830
Be that as it may, I just can’t bear to let go of your hand

392
00:29:01.880 --> 00:29:06.780
I’ve still gotta move, even if I’m alone I’ll walk along

393
00:29:06.820 --> 00:29:12.050
Just promise that you’ll still keep 
an eye on me when I am gone

394
00:29:16.700 --> 00:29:21.580
As soon as I woke up, couldn’t get it off my mind

395
00:29:21.630 --> 00:29:26.330
“Why the hell’s it so hot? I can hardly breathe!”

396
00:29:26.330 --> 00:29:32.840
It’s been quite a while, 
but those thoughts just won’t seem to let go

397
00:29:32.840 --> 00:29:36.720
But hey, what do I know?

398
00:29:37.670 --> 00:29:42.580
Guess I want a taste of that thing people call a “runner’s high”

399
00:29:42.580 --> 00:29:47.460
Think I chased too hard, and ended up leaving myself behind

400
00:29:47.510 --> 00:29:52.440
All I want’s a taste of a dream that a sentence can’t define

401
00:29:52.440 --> 00:29:57.640
Stick right by my side, and I can run, run, run until I die
